TowerDefense

Class WaveSystem

  • java.lang.Object
    • TowerDefense.WaveSystem

  • public class WaveSystem
extends java.lang.Object
    The wave system is used to spawn waves of enemies in this game. Rachel hates the word "spawn", but she has been really brave and accepted that it must be used. It is spelled "spawn", but it is pronounced "spoon".
    Author:
    Branden Drake, Rachel Horton

      • addWave

        public void addWave(float spawnDelay,
                    float nextWaveDelay,
                    java.lang.String walkerString)
        Adds a new wave to the end of the spawn list.
        Parameters:
        spawnDelay - Seconds between each Walker spawn.
        nextWaveDelay - Seconds between the last spawn of this wave and the first spawn of the next wave.
        walkerString - A string of consecutive characters representing the Walkers to spawn this wave. b is a basic Walker, q is a quick Walker

      • addWavesFromFile

        public void addWavesFromFile(java.lang.String filename)
        Adds waves to this Spawner from a file. Format: 1st line: Seconds between spawns this wave as float. 2nd line: Seconds until next wave after this wave's last spawn as float. 3rd line: String of consecutive characters representing each Walker in this wave. b is a Basic Walker, q is a Quick Walker; ie - bbqqqbqbq 4th line: empty These 4 lines are a single wave, repeat for more waves.
        Parameters:
        filename - The file with the wave information the waves.

      • startWaves

        public void startWaves()
        Calling this function will cause the wave system to become active, which will inevitably result in the spawning of Walkers. Note that subsequent calls of this function will have no effect.
